vectorData.altText: 2. The parts of the brain that occupy the anterior cranial fossae are the ____________ _____________.
That is incorrect. Click here      to learn the answer, then come back to try again.
That’s right! The frontal lobes occupy the anterior cranial fossae.

The foramen magnum is the site of the junction of the spinal cord with the brainstem. The brainstem is in close relationship to the clivus, ventrally.  The rostral end of the brainstem, the midbrain, occupies the tentorial notch.  The cerebellum is attached to the dorsal aspect of the brainstem and occupies the posterior fossa. The occipital lobes sit on the superior surface of the tentorium cerebelli, the temporal lobes occupy the middle cranial fossa and the frontal lobes occupy the anterior cranial fossa.
The tentorium cerebelli subdivides the cranial cavity into a supratentorial compartment, which contains the cerebral hemispheres, and an infratentorial compartment, which contains the brainstem and cerebellum.
Now you can relate the components of the brain to the bones and dura.
